        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 28 at 1:32PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 131 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles east of Downtown Asheville, or near Swannanoa, moving south at
5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Black Mountain, Swannanoa, and Fairview In Buncombe County.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
